<paragraph id="8BD93693F215FF92F9F7F95440DA7EFB" blockId="0.[166,1023,1711,1738]" box="[166,1023,1711,1738]" pageId="0" pageNumber="489">
<typeStatus id="54DD8831F215FF92F9F7F95443C47EFB" box="[166,225,1712,1738]" pageId="0" pageNumber="489">Type</typeStatus>
species: 
<taxonomicName id="4C664D10F215FF92F819F94B41EA7EFB" authority="Keiser, 1951" authorityName="Keiser" authorityYear="1951" box="[328,719,1711,1738]" class="Insecta" family="Ctenostylidae" genus="Ramuliseta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="489" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="palpifera">
<emphasis id="B912EA81F215FF92F819F94B411D7EF8" box="[328,568,1711,1737]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="489">Ramuliseta palpifera</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFF74B62F215FF92FB6EF94B41EA7EFB" author="Keiser, F." box="[575,719,1711,1738]" pageId="0" pageNumber="489" pagination="113 - 124" refId="ref5039" refString="Keiser, F. 1951. Die Unterfamilie der Lochmostyliinae (Dipt., Pyrgotidae) nebst Beschreibung einer neuen Gattung und Art aus dem indo-australischen Faunengebiet. Mitteilungen der Schweizerischen Entomologischen Gesellschaft, 24, 113 - 124." type="journal article" year="1951">Keiser, 1951</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(by original designation).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD93693F215FF93F98AF90B475B7B1B" blockId="0.[166,1225,1775,1834]" lastBlockId="1.[174,1233,175,1066]" lastPageId="1" lastPageNumber="490" pageId="0" pageNumber="489">
Diagnosis. The flies of the genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C664D10F215FF92FB2FF90B40247F38" authorityName="Keiser" authorityYear="1951" box="[638,769,1775,1801]" class="Insecta" family="Ctenostylidae" genus="Ramuliseta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="489" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B912EA81F215FF92FB2FF90B40247F38" box="[638,769,1775,1801]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="489">Ramuliseta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, similarly to the other Higher 
<taxonomicName id="4C664D10F215FF92FD3FF90B43CA7F18" authorityName="E.Newman" authorityYear="1834" pageId="0" pageNumber="496" rank="superFamily" superFamily="Tephritoidea">Tephritoidea</taxonomicName>
(sensu 
<bibRefCitation id="EFF74B62F215FF92F819F8F441257F1B" author="Korneyev, V. A." box="[328,512,1807,1834]" pageId="0" pageNumber="489" pagination="3 - 22" refId="ref5132" refString="Korneyev, V. A. 1999. Phylogenetic relationships among the families of the superfamily Tephritoidea. In: Aluja, M., Norrbom, A. L., eds. Fruit Flies (Tephritidae): Phylogeny and Evolution of Behavior, CRC Press, Boca Raton, 3 - 22." type="book chapter" year="1999">Korneyev, 1999</bibRefCitation>
) have pictured wings and telesopic ovipositor of the females. Similarly to the other ctenostylids, they can be easily distinguished by the combination of lacking ocelli, vestigial proboscis, incomplete vein Sc, cell cup closed by arcuate crossvein without triangular lobe along vein CuA 
<subScript id="17E234D6F214FF93FBD5FEE641A97921" attach="left" box="[644,652,258,272]" fontSize="6" pageId="1" pageNumber="490">2</subScript>
+A 
<subScript id="17E234D6F214FF93FBE3FEE6419F7921" attach="left" box="[690,698,258,272]" fontSize="6" pageId="1" pageNumber="490">1</subScript>
, strongly dimorphic arista (dendritical in females, simple and short pubescent in males), transverse prosternum, proepisternum bare or at most with one fine seta, spiracles round and open, without marginal fringe, anterior notopleural seta lacking, male genitalia with surstyli indistinguishable, without prensisetae, phallus spimple, tubular, with reduced glans, and female with aculeus simple, tubular, non-sclerotized, with small, blunt and short setulose, non-piercing cercal unit. Flies of the genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C664D10F214FF93F9ADFE4B425A79F8" authorityName="Keiser" authorityYear="1951" box="[252,383,431,457]" class="Insecta" family="Ctenostylidae" genus="Ramuliseta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="490" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B912EA81F214FF93F9ADFE4B425A79F8" box="[252,383,431,457]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="490">Ramuliseta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have well developed palp as in species of Neotropical 
<taxonomicName id="4C664D10F214FF93FD44FE5443CC79DB" authority="Aczel, 1956" authorityName="Aczel" authorityYear="1956" class="Insecta" family="Ctenostylidae" genus="Furciseta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="490" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B912EA81F214FF93FD44FE54475A79F8" box="[1045,1151,432,457]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="490">Furciseta</emphasis>
Aczél, 1956
</taxonomicName>
, 
<collectingRegion id="49A2F871F214FF93F9A9FE2B427F79D8" box="[248,346,463,489]" country="Democratic Republic of the Congo" name="Orientale" pageId="1" pageNumber="490">Oriental</collectingRegion>
<taxonomicName id="4C664D10F214FF93F837FE2B41E079DB" authority="Barraclough, 1995" authorityName="Barraclough" authorityYear="1995" box="[358,709,463,490]" class="Insecta" family="Ctenostylidae" genus="Nepaliseta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="490" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B912EA81F214FF93F837FE2B42FA79D8" box="[358,479,463,489]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="490">Nepaliseta</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFF74B62F214FF93F8BBFE2B41E079DB" author="Barraclough, D. A." box="[490,709,463,490]" pageId="1" pageNumber="490" pagination="135 - 139" refId="ref4892" refString="Barraclough, D. A. 1995. Nepaliseta mirabilis, a remarkable new genus and species of Ctenostylidae (Diptera: Schizophora) from Nepal. Annals of the Natal Museum, 36, 135 - 139." type="journal article" year="1995">Barraclough, 1995</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C664D10F214FF93FA59FE2B474579DB" authority="Yang, 1995" authorityName="Yang" authorityYear="1995" box="[776,1120,463,490]" class="Insecta" family="Pyrgotidae" genus="Sinolochmostylia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="490" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B912EA81F214FF93FA59FE2B40E879D8" box="[776,973,463,489]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="490">Sinolochmostylia</emphasis>
Yang, 1995
</taxonomicName>
differing from them all by veins R 
<subScript id="17E234D6F214FF93F89EFDE642CF7A21" attach="left" box="[463,490,514,528]" fontSize="6" pageId="1" pageNumber="490">2+3</subScript>
and R 
<subScript id="17E234D6F214FF93FB67FDE641747A21" attach="left" box="[566,593,514,528]" fontSize="6" pageId="1" pageNumber="490">4+5</subScript>
subparallel: distance along costal margin between R 
<subScript id="17E234D6F214FF93FDE7FDE647F57A21" attach="left" box="[1206,1232,514,528]" fontSize="6" pageId="1" pageNumber="490">2+3</subScript>
and R 
<subScript id="17E234D6F214FF93F9A4FDC6422A7A01" attach="left" box="[245,271,546,560]" fontSize="6" pageId="1" pageNumber="490">4+5</subScript>
less than twice distance between R 
<subScript id="17E234D6F214FF93FBE3FDC641E87A01" attach="left" box="[690,717,546,560]" fontSize="6" pageId="1" pageNumber="490">4+5</subScript>
and M (strongly divergent, with R 
<subScript id="17E234D6F214FF93FD3CFDC647A27A01" attach="left" box="[1133,1159,546,560]" fontSize="6" pageId="1" pageNumber="490">2+3</subScript>
conspicuously bowed anterobasally in 
<taxonomicName id="4C664D10F214FF93FB6CFDD441827A78" authorityName="Aczel" authorityYear="1956" box="[573,679,560,585]" class="Insecta" family="Ctenostylidae" genus="Furciseta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="490" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B912EA81F214FF93FB6CFDD441827A78" box="[573,679,560,585]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="490">Furciseta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C664D10F214FF93FBE5FDCB40087A78" authorityName="Barraclough" authorityYear="1995" box="[692,813,559,585]" class="Insecta" family="Ctenostylidae" genus="Nepaliseta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="490" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B912EA81F214FF93FBE5FDCB40087A78" box="[692,813,559,585]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="490">Nepaliseta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="4C664D10F214FF93FA3EFDCB47117A78" authorityName="Yang" authorityYear="1995" box="[879,1076,559,585]" class="Insecta" family="Pyrgotidae" genus="Sinolochmostylia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="490" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B912EA81F214FF93FA3EFDCB47117A78" box="[879,1076,559,585]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="490">Sinolochmostylia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). The species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C664D10F214FF93F99DFDAB426A7A58" authorityName="Keiser" authorityYear="1951" box="[204,335,591,617]" class="Insecta" family="Ctenostylidae" genus="Ramuliseta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="490" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B912EA81F214FF93F99DFDAB426A7A58" box="[204,335,591,617]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="490">Ramuliseta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differ from 
<taxonomicName id="4C664D10F214FF93F88CFDB441627A58" authorityName="Aczel" authorityYear="1956" box="[477,583,592,617]" class="Insecta" family="Ctenostylidae" genus="Furciseta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="490" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B912EA81F214FF93F88CFDB441627A58" box="[477,583,592,617]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="490">Furciseta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
also by having frons of males unmodified, not strongly narrowed (sexually dimorphic in 
<taxonomicName id="4C664D10F214FF93FB15FD94418B7AB8" authorityName="Aczel" authorityYear="1956" box="[580,686,624,649]" class="Insecta" family="Ctenostylidae" genus="Furciseta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="490" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B912EA81F214FF93FB15FD94418B7AB8" box="[580,686,624,649]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="490">Furciseta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
very narrow in males and unmodified in females) and vein M developed in distal half of cell bm (vein M lacking basally of crossvein bm-cu in 
<taxonomicName id="4C664D10F214FF93F871FD5442AF7AF8" authorityName="Aczel" authorityYear="1956" box="[288,394,688,713]" class="Insecta" family="Ctenostylidae" genus="Furciseta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="490" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B912EA81F214FF93F871FD5442AF7AF8" box="[288,394,688,713]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="490">Furciseta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). The species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C664D10F214FF93FB18FD4B41E97AF8" authorityName="Keiser" authorityYear="1951" box="[585,716,687,713]" class="Insecta" family="Ctenostylidae" genus="Ramuliseta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="490" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B912EA81F214FF93FB18FD4B41E97AF8" box="[585,716,687,713]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="490">Ramuliseta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differ from 
<taxonomicName id="4C664D10F214FF93FA08FD4B40F77AF8" authorityName="Barraclough" authorityYear="1995" box="[857,978,687,713]" class="Insecta" family="Ctenostylidae" genus="Nepaliseta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="490" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B912EA81F214FF93FA08FD4B40F77AF8" box="[857,978,687,713]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="490">Nepaliseta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C664D10F214FF93FD5AFD4B47F57AF8" authorityName="Yang" authorityYear="1995" box="[1035,1232,687,713]" class="Insecta" family="Pyrgotidae" genus="Sinolochmostylia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="490" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B912EA81F214FF93FD5AFD4B47F57AF8" box="[1035,1232,687,713]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="490">Sinolochmostylia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by having flagellomere 1 of females elongate, with narrowed apical projection, and arista with multiple branching (in 
<taxonomicName id="4C664D10F214FF93F8AFFD0B41527B38" authorityName="Barraclough" authorityYear="1995" box="[510,631,751,777]" class="Insecta" family="Ctenostylidae" genus="Nepaliseta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="490" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B912EA81F214FF93F8AFFD0B41527B38" box="[510,631,751,777]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="490">Nepaliseta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C664D10F214FF93FBE3FD0B40527B38" authorityName="Yang" authorityYear="1995" box="[690,887,751,777]" class="Insecta" family="Pyrgotidae" genus="Sinolochmostylia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="490" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B912EA81F214FF93FBE3FD0B40527B38" box="[690,887,751,777]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="490">Sinolochmostylia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, flagellomere 1 of females almost spherical, without apical projection, and arista extremely modified, disk-like).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD93693F214FF93F9B2FCCB42517B58" blockId="1.[174,1233,175,1066]" pageId="1" pageNumber="490">
The genus was described by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFF74B62F214FF93FB11FCCB40027B7B" author="Barraclough, D. A." box="[576,807,815,842]" pageId="1" pageNumber="490" pagination="5 - 14" refId="ref4848" refString="Barraclough, D. A. 1994. A review of the Afrotropical Ctenostylidae (Diptera: Schizophora:? Tephritoidea), with redescription of Ramuliseta lindneri Keiser, 1952. Annals of the Natal Museum, 35, 5 - 14." type="journal article" year="1994">Barraclough (1994)</bibRefCitation>
in details, and I do not repeat the description here.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD93693F214FF93F9B2FC9441A57B9B" blockId="1.[174,1233,175,1066]" pageId="1" pageNumber="490">
D i s t r i b u t i o n. Afrotropical (
<collectingCountry id="F3717603F214FF93FB12FC8B41B87BB8" box="[579,669,879,905]" name="Nigeria" pageId="1" pageNumber="490">Nigeria</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="F3717603F214FF93FB84FC8B40677BB8" box="[725,834,879,905]" name="Tanzania" pageId="1" pageNumber="490">Tanzania</collectingCountry>
to 
<collectingCountry id="F3717603F214FF93FA37FC8B40D87BB8" box="[870,1021,879,905]" name="South Africa" pageId="1" pageNumber="490">South Africa</collectingCountry>
; 
<collectingCountry id="F3717603F214FF93FD56FC8B47B37BBB" box="[1031,1174,879,906]" name="Madagascar" pageId="1" pageNumber="490">Madagascar</collectingCountry>
) and Oriental Region (Lesser Sunda Islands).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD93693F214FF93F9B2FC4B402A7C1B" blockId="1.[174,1233,175,1066]" pageId="1" pageNumber="490">
The genus now includes 3 species: Palaeotropical 
<taxonomicName id="4C664D10F214FF93FA6FFC4B47F57BFB" authority="Keiser, 1951" authorityName="Keiser" authorityYear="1951" box="[830,1232,943,970]" class="Insecta" family="Ctenostylidae" genus="Ramuliseta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="490" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="palpifera">
<emphasis id="B912EA81F214FF93FA6FFC4B47167BF8" box="[830,1075,943,969]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="490">Ramuliseta palpifera</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFF74B62F214FF93FD6CFC4B47F57BFB" author="Keiser, F." box="[1085,1232,943,970]" pageId="1" pageNumber="490" pagination="113 - 124" refId="ref5039" refString="Keiser, F. 1951. Die Unterfamilie der Lochmostyliinae (Dipt., Pyrgotidae) nebst Beschreibung einer neuen Gattung und Art aus dem indo-australischen Faunengebiet. Mitteilungen der Schweizerischen Entomologischen Gesellschaft, 24, 113 - 124." type="journal article" year="1951">Keiser, 1951</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(= 
<taxonomicName id="4C664D10F214FF93F980FC3442C97BDB" authority="Keiser, 1952" authorityName="Keiser" authorityYear="1952" box="[209,492,975,1002]" class="Insecta" family="Ctenostylidae" genus="Ramuliseta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="490" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lindneri">
<emphasis id="B912EA81F214FF93F980FC34426B7BD8" box="[209,334,975,1001]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="490">R. lindneri</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFF74B62F214FF93F807FC2B42C97BDB" author="Keiser, F." box="[342,492,975,1002]" pageId="1" pageNumber="490" pagination="325 - 327" refId="ref5079" refString="Keiser, F. 1952. Ramuliseta lindneri n. sp. eine Lochmostyliine aus Ostafrika (Dipt. Pyrgotidae). (Ergebnisse der Deutschen Zoologischen Ostafrika-Expedition 1951 / 52, Gruppe Lindner, Nr. 1). Bonner Zoologische Beitrage, 3 (314), 325 - 327." type="journal article" year="1952">Keiser, 1952</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
), Afrotropical 
<taxonomicName id="4C664D10F214FF93FBCAFC34470B7BD8" authority="Hennig, 1960" authorityName="Hennig" authorityYear="1960" box="[667,1070,975,1001]" class="Insecta" family="Ctenostylidae" genus="Ramuliseta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="490" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="madagascariensis">
<emphasis id="B912EA81F214FF93FBCAFC3440A27BD8" box="[667,903,975,1001]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="490">R. madagascariensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFF74B62F214FF93FADEFC2B470B7BD8" author="Hennig, W." box="[911,1070,975,1001]" pageId="1" pageNumber="490" pagination="321 - 353" refId="ref5006" refString="Hennig, W. 1960. Pyrgotidae de Madagascar (Diptera). Memoires de l'Institut Scientifique de Madagascar. Ser. E, 11 (1959), 321 - 353." type="journal article" year="1960">Hennig, 1960</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C664D10F214FF93FD3DFC3447F47BD8" authority="Korneyev, 2015" authorityName="V. Korneyev" authorityYear="2015" box="[1132,1233,975,1001]" class="Insecta" family="Ctenostylidae" genus="Ramuliseta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="490" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dolini" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="B912EA81F214FF93FD3DFC3447F47BD8" box="[1132,1233,975,1001]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="490">R. dolini</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A22157FAF214FF93F9FFFC1443CA7C3B" box="[174,239,1008,1034]" pageId="1" pageNumber="490" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
(
<collectingCountry id="F3717603F214FF93F850FC0B42B07C3B" box="[257,405,1007,1034]" name="Madagascar" pageId="1" pageNumber="490">Madagascar</collectingCountry>
). The Oriental 
<taxonomicName id="4C664D10F214FF93FB1DFC14405C7C38" authority="Korneyev, 2001" authorityName="Korneyev" authorityYear="2001" box="[588,889,1007,1034]" class="Insecta" family="Ctenostylidae" genus="Ramuliseta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="490" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="thaica">
<emphasis id="B912EA81F214FF93FB1DFC1441937C38" box="[588,694,1007,1033]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="490">R. thaica</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFF74B62F214FF93FB91FC14405C7C38" author="Korneyev, V. A." box="[704,889,1007,1034]" pageId="1" pageNumber="490" pagination="47 - 60" refId="ref5188" refString="Korneyev, V. A. 2001. New records of Oriental Ctenostylidae (Diptera, Acalyptrata), with discussion of the position of the family. Vestnik Zoologii, 35 (3), 47 - 60." type="journal article" year="2001">Korneyev, 2001</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
belongs elsewhere, either to 
<taxonomicName id="4C664D10F214FF93F9FFFBEB42567C18" authorityName="Yang" authorityYear="1995" box="[174,371,1039,1065]" class="Insecta" family="Pyrgotidae" genus="Sinolochmostylia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="490" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B912EA81F214FF93F9FFFBEB42567C18" box="[174,371,1039,1065]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="490">Sinolochmostylia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
or 
<taxonomicName id="4C664D10F214FF93F8CBFBEB41367C18" authorityName="Barraclough" authorityYear="1995" box="[410,531,1039,1065]" class="Insecta" family="Ctenostylidae" genus="Nepaliseta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="490" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B912EA81F214FF93F8CBFBEB41367C18" box="[410,531,1039,1065]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="490">Nepaliseta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Korneyev, in prep.).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C37C6518F214FF93F9FFFBB542ED7C57" box="[174,456,1104,1126]" pageId="1" pageNumber="490" type="key">
<paragraph id="8BD93693F214FF93F9FFFBB542ED7C57" blockId="1.[174,1233,1104,1386]" box="[174,456,1104,1126]" pageId="1" pageNumber="490">
