<emphasis id="B912EA81F214FF93F9FFFBB542ED7C57" bold="true" box="[174,456,1104,1126]" pageId="1" pageNumber="490">
Key to species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C664D10F214FF93F809FBB442ED7C57" authorityName="Keiser" authorityYear="1951" box="[344,456,1104,1126]" class="Insecta" family="Ctenostylidae" genus="Ramuliseta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="490" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B912EA81F214FF93F809FBB442ED7C57" bold="true" box="[344,456,1104,1126]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="490">Ramuliseta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C37C6518F214FF93F9FFFB8947F47D5B" pageId="1" pageNumber="490" type="key">
<keyStep id="30922E36F214FF93F9FFFB8947F47CC6" pageId="1" pageNumber="490">
<paragraph id="8BD93693F214FF93F9FFFB8947F57C8C" blockId="1.[174,1233,1104,1386]" pageId="1" pageNumber="490">
<keyLead id="309795A6F214FF93F9FFFB8947F57C8C" pageId="1" pageNumber="490">
1. Smaller (wing shorter than 
<quantity id="4C9E9B76F214FF93FB52FB89416B7CB2" box="[515,590,1133,1155]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.5" pageId="1" pageNumber="490" unit="mm" value="5.5">5.5 mm</quantity>
) dark brown flies; wing with brown wing pattern; cell R 
<subScript id="17E234D6F214FF93FD3AFB9847A57CB8" attach="left" box="[1131,1152,1148,1161]" fontSize="5" pageId="1" pageNumber="490">4+5</subScript>
entirely brown in apical half (
<figureCitation id="135D2A16F214FF93F894FB6E42D07C91" box="[453,501,1162,1184]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="1.[174,207,1795,1817]" captionTargetBox="[216,1185,1632,1756]" captionTargetId="figure-569@1.[212,1195,1626,1784]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="Fig. 1. Ramuliseta, wing: 1 — R. dolini sp.n.; 2 — R. madagascariensis; 3 — R. palpifera (arrows show key characters)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6452667" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6452667/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="490">fig. 1</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="135D2A16F214FF93FB51FB6E412E7CAE" box="[512,523,1162,1183]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="4.[166,199,750,772]" captionTargetBox="[272,1051,199,697]" captionTargetId="figure-449@4.[228,1133,172,735]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Fig. 3. Ramuliseta madagascariensis, paralectotype ♀: 1 — head dorsal, 2 — same, right; 3 — wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6452673" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6452673/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="490">
<emphasis id="B912EA81F214FF93FB51FB6E412E7CAE" box="[512,523,1162,1183]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="490">3</emphasis>
</figureCitation>
). Mainland sub-Saharan Africa, 
<collectingRegion id="49A2F871F214FF93FA17FB6E47347C91" box="[838,1041,1162,1184]" country="Indonesia" name="Nusa Tenggara Timur" pageId="1" pageNumber="490">Lesser Sunda Islands</collectingRegion>
. ................................. ..................................................................................................................... 
<taxonomicName id="4C664D10F214FF93FA2EFB4347F57C8C" authority="(Keiser, 1951)" baseAuthorityName="Keiser" baseAuthorityYear="1951" box="[895,1232,1191,1213]" class="Insecta" family="Ctenostylidae" genus="Ramuliseta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="490" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="palpifera">
<emphasis id="B912EA81F214FF93FA2EFB4347617C8D" box="[895,1092,1191,1212]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="490">Ramuliseta palpifera</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFF74B62F214FF93FD01FB4347EF7C8C" author="Keiser, F." box="[1104,1226,1191,1213]" pageId="1" pageNumber="490" pagination="113 - 124" refId="ref5039" refString="Keiser, F. 1951. Die Unterfamilie der Lochmostyliinae (Dipt., Pyrgotidae) nebst Beschreibung einer neuen Gattung und Art aus dem indo-australischen Faunengebiet. Mitteilungen der Schweizerischen Entomologischen Gesellschaft, 24, 113 - 124." type="journal article" year="1951">Keiser, 1951</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD93693F214FF93F9FFFB2047F47CC6" blockId="1.[174,1233,1104,1386]" pageId="1" pageNumber="490">
<keyLead id="309795A6F214FF93F9FFFB2047F47CC6" pageId="1" pageNumber="490">
— Larger (wing shorter than 
<quantity id="4C9E9B76F214FF93F8A4FB20411A7CEB" box="[501,575,1220,1242]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.5" pageId="1" pageNumber="490" unit="mm" value="6.5">6.5 mm</quantity>
) yellow flies; wing with yellow wing pattern; cell R 
<subScript id="17E234D6F214FF93FD4EFB3747117CD1" attach="left" box="[1055,1076,1235,1248]" fontSize="5" pageId="1" pageNumber="490">4+5</subScript>
with one or two hyaline areas in apical half (
<figureCitation id="135D2A16F214FF93FB52FB05416C7CC7" box="[515,585,1249,1271]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="1.[174,207,1795,1817]" captionTargetBox="[216,1185,1632,1756]" captionTargetId="figure-569@1.[212,1195,1626,1784]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="Fig. 1. Ramuliseta, wing: 1 — R. dolini sp.n.; 2 — R. madagascariensis; 3 — R. palpifera (arrows show key characters)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6452667" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6452667/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="490">
fig. 1, 
<emphasis id="B912EA81F214FF93FB6FFB05416C7CC7" box="[574,585,1249,1270]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="490">1</emphasis>
</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="135D2A16F214FF93FB05FB05417A7CC7" box="[596,607,1249,1270]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="3.[175,208,822,844]" captionTargetBox="[260,1144,174,801]" captionTargetId="figure-371@3.[255,1144,174,810]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Fig. 2. Ramuliseta dolini sp. n., holotype ♀: 1 — habitus, lateral view; 2–5 — head (2 — left, 3 — anterior, 4 — dorsal view); 6 — wing; 7 — mesonotum, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6452669" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6452669/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="490">
<emphasis id="B912EA81F214FF93FB05FB05417A7CC7" box="[596,607,1249,1270]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="490">2</emphasis>
</figureCitation>
). 
<collectingCountry id="F3717603F214FF93FB22FB0541FB7CC6" box="[627,734,1249,1271]" name="Madagascar" pageId="1" pageNumber="490">Madagascar</collectingCountry>
..................................................................................... 2.
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="30922E36F214FF93F9FFFB1947F47D5B" pageId="1" pageNumber="490">
<paragraph id="8BD93693F214FF93F9FFFB1947F57D01" blockId="1.[174,1233,1104,1386]" pageId="1" pageNumber="490">
<keyLead id="309795A6F214FF93F9FFFB1947F57D01" pageId="1" pageNumber="490">
2. Wing apex hyaline; cell r 
<subScript id="17E234D6F214FF93F8A2FAE8412D7D28" attach="left" box="[499,520,1292,1305]" fontSize="5" pageId="1" pageNumber="490">4+5</subScript>
distal of crossvein dm-cu with two hyaline areas separated by rounded brown spot between them (
<figureCitation id="135D2A16F214FF93F8AEFAFE410A7D01" box="[511,559,1306,1328]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="1.[174,207,1795,1817]" captionTargetBox="[216,1185,1632,1756]" captionTargetId="figure-569@1.[212,1195,1626,1784]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="Fig. 1. Ramuliseta, wing: 1 — R. dolini sp.n.; 2 — R. madagascariensis; 3 — R. palpifera (arrows show key characters)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6452667" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6452667/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="490">fig. 1</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="135D2A16F214FF93FB6BFAFE41607D1E" box="[570,581,1306,1327]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="3.[175,208,822,844]" captionTargetBox="[260,1144,174,801]" captionTargetId="figure-371@3.[255,1144,174,810]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Fig. 2. Ramuliseta dolini sp. n., holotype ♀: 1 — habitus, lateral view; 2–5 — head (2 — left, 3 — anterior, 4 — dorsal view); 6 — wing; 7 — mesonotum, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6452669" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6452669/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="490">
<emphasis id="B912EA81F214FF93FB6BFAFE41607D1E" box="[570,581,1306,1327]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="490">2</emphasis>
